con:method.name: get
con:method.con:description: Retrieve git log data from the versioning server for up to 10 revisions. Add optional parameters to filter to specific revisions.

con:parameter.con:name: eid
con:parameter.con:description: The entity id of the versioned resource.

con:parameter.con:name: author
con:parameter.con:description: The author that triggered the revision.

con:parameter.con:name: action
con:parameter.con:description: An indicator of which type of user action originally triggered the revision (ie, "Edit" or "Save").

con:parameter.con:name: description
con:parameter.con:description: Searches the commit messages of the revisions in git for partial matches with the "Changes" string.

con:parameter.con:name: before
con:parameter.con:description: Specify this stringified UTC timestamp parameter to only show revisions that were logged before this time. This is used by the versioning server to retrieve the next set of revisions chronologically. Format is "2015-08-01T 10 20 00-04 00"

con:parameter.con:name: until
con:parameter.con:description: Specify this stringified UTC timestamp parameter to only show revisions that were logged before this time. This is used by the versioning server to filter out revisions that are too recent. Format is "2015-08-01T 10 20 00-04 00"

con:parameter.con:name: since
con:parameter.con:description: Specify this stringified UTC timestamp parameter to only show revisions that were logged after this time. This is used by the versioning server to filter out revisions that are too old. Format is "2015-08-01T 10 20 00-04 00"

con:representation.con:description: Server error.

con:method.name: get
con:method.con:description: Retrieve collection of all root entities (journals) for authenticated user. Or by using the depth query parameter it is possible to return entities beyond the root level. It is also possible to filter entities by type or by modification date (start or end), as well as paginating results using limit and offset.

con:parameter.con:name: include
con:parameter.con:description: List of categories to include in query. Valid values are "mine" for items owned by the current user, "shared" for items that have been shared with the current user, "other" for items owned by other users but the current user has access to through tenant-wide-access (if enabled), "trashed", "untrashed", "trashedAncestor" (to show items normally discarded if they have a trashed ancestor), "template" and "nontemplate", "starred" and "unstarred". Multiple parameters can be specified in comma separated list. If the parameter is not specified the defaults are "mine", "shared", "other", "untrashed", "nontemplate", "starred" and "unstarred". For /children this will use the same default but also include "trashedAncestor". Note that if using "trashedAncestor" you must also specify "trashed" and/or "untrashed".

con:parameter.con:name: type
con:parameter.con:description: Comma separated list of element types to return. Options are: journal, experiment, abstract, discussion, introduction, protocol, results, chemicaldrawing, spreadsheet, presentation, imageresource, viewonly, pdf, acronym, texttemplate. If no parameter is specified this will default to journal, or to all element types if /children is being requested.

con:parameter.con:name: exclude
con:parameter.con:description: List of element types to exclude from results, applicable to request for /children. See above for list of valid element types.

con:parameter.con:name: depth
con:parameter.con:description: Number of descendant levels of items to show. If parameter is not specified it will default to 0.

con:parameter.con:name: start
con:parameter.con:description: Specify this UTC timestamp parameter to only show items with a modification date after this time. Note that parent items will also be shown to give full context to each entity, even if the parent has a modification timestamp prior to the value of this parameter. Format: 2015-08-01T10:20:30

con:parameter.con:name: end
con:parameter.con:description: Specify this UTC timestamp parameter to only show items with a modification date before this time. Format: 2015-08-07T10:20:30

con:parameter.con:name: limit
con:parameter.con:description: Maximum number of items to show. If depth is greater than 0 this limit applies to child items.

con:parameter.con:name: offset
con:parameter.con:description: To be used in conjunction with limit, this parameter is the number of items to be skipped before returning data. This is in order for a client to query for data in batches rather than consuming all data at once.

con:parameter.con:name: application
con:parameter.con:description: This parameter must be specified if you are wanting to obtain layout information for the entity.

con:representation.con:description: OK
